1. what is cloud computing
   Cloud computing is a service that is avaliable over the internet e.g DB storage, Launch applications and other IT services. It is Pay as you go pricing

--Amazon Ec2
It is one most popular service.
EC2 = Elastic Cloud Compute = Infrastructure as a Service (Iaas)
 --Key Features
    1. Renting virtual machines(EC2)
    2. Storing data on virtual drives(EBS)
    3. Distributing load across machines(ELB)
--Dedicated Instance
  Dedicated Instances are Amazon EC2 instances that run in a virtual private cloud (VPC) on hardware that's dedicated to a single customer. Dedicated Instances that belong to different AWS accounts are physically isolated at a hardware level, even if those accounts are linked to a single payer account

--AWS disaster recovery solutions
Multi-site-active-active
You can run your workload simultaneously in multiple Regions as part of a multi-site active/active. There is no such thing as failover in this scenario

AWS is fully responsible for securing the infrastructure that it provides to the customers

Which design principle of AWS Cloud Architecture offers distribution of workloads among multiple Availability Zones ?

Design for Failure 
AWS suggests that you distribute your workloads across multiple AZs. In case of any single AZ failure, your application will be available and can be accessed continuously

AWS Cloud benefits
Capital expenditure(Capex) translates to variable expenditure
Companies gain better agility for their business

What is Amazon DynamoDB
